description:
Split Decision



Aired on 08/26/2011, Narrated by Jonathan Aris



On 12 December 1985, Arrow Air Flight 1285 a Douglas DC-8-63CF, carrying troops of the US Army's 101st Airborne Division, stalls and crashes just seconds after taking off from Gander International Airport in Canada, killing all 256 people on board. The cause of the crash remains disputed.
